column1: GISP2 Ice core methane concentrations (May 5
Description:

Methane (CH4) concentrations from discrete samples of the GISP2 ice core measured by Oregon State University (OSU) and Pennsylvania State University (PSU). PSU measurements include depths 2167.89 – 2204.00m
column2: OSU measured all other depths. OSU wet-extraction techniques are described by (Mitchell et al. 2013)
column3: PSU are described by (Fudge et al. 2013). Methane mixing ratios are measured on an Agilent 6890N gas chromotograph
column4: and reported on the NOAA04 calibration scale (Dlugokencky et al. 2005).

column1: All depths are mean sample depth in meters below surface
column2: ages are on the GICC05modelext gas chronology in years before 2000 (b2k) (Seierstad et al. 2014). Reported methane data are corrected for (1) system blanks derived from bubble-free ice
column4: and (3) offsets between sampling campaigns in 2014
column7: and 2019. Offsets between sampling efforts were determined by nearest neighbor and replicate measurements of GISP2 samples
column8: and via WAIS Divide ice core samples measured concurrently. The campaign-specific correction is 5ppb for data measured in 2014
column10: and 0ppb for data in 2018 and 2019. No offsets were identified between PSU and OSU measurements. Campaign offsets are attributed to drift in calibration standards and other elements of the analytical setup.

column1: Production of CH4  during OSU during melt extraction was identified and characterized by (Lee et al. 2020). Methane values corrected for excess CH4 production (on top of the blank
column3: and sampling campaign corrections) are reported separately.
